Child: Mix together the flour, salt, and baking powder. Set aside. Beat the eggs well. Gradually beat the sugar into the eggs, then beat in the margarine and chocolate. Mix in the flour mixture. Stir in the vanilla and nuts, and place in a baking pan.
Adult: Preheat the oven to 350°F.
Child: Bake for 25 minutes. Let cool, then dust with confectioners' sugar and cut into squares.
